    {
      "id": "1526915164496990248",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-15T11:35:43.928+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "- rv32ima_zicsr core in 6502-compatible pinout\n- 6502/6510 clone (cycle-accurate, now hopefully with the bus timing fixed)\n- C64 PLA\n- Nanoprocessor clone, 8-bit educational CPU, LED blinker\n- The two [FeatherLane](https://codeberg.org/TholinVali/FeatherLane) -generated layouts: rv32i core and a VERY simple CPU that is a 32-bit version of [MCPU](https://github.com/cpldcpu/MCPU/tree/master) \n- C64 SID clone\n- C64 SID clone, but I added FM synthesis features on top (fully backwards-compatible)\n- General-purpose IO peripheral block you can hook up to an existing CPU\n- Test NTSC signal generator (now in color - I have it set up displaying some pixel art or pride flags)\n- The R2R DACs (hopefully the output stage isn’t power hungry anymore)\n- Another copy of 32-bit MCPU, except its using Dynamic DFFs (we’ll see how that works out on this process node)\n- The Palette, which contains samples of everything I can draw and experiments with metal spacing - will give microscope images of this to any artists that agree to create silicon art for me in the future, to give them more options for \"colors\"",
      "author": {
        "id": "220639106915368960",
        "name": "tholin",
